2. Institutional Mandate

2.1 Foundational Premise

The gods formed Kamile from optimal earth and one merciless idea. This constitutes, under prevailing metaphysical procurement standards, both a divine endowment and an unfunded mandate.

The mandate may be stated as follows:

To identify latent human form within inert terrestrial mass, extract it through disciplined craft, and animate it through irreversible personal diminishment, while maintaining the appearance of voluntary artistic fulfilment.

2.2 Mission Statement

The mission of the Kamile Clay-Man Continuity Initiative is to advance the responsible fabrication of clay-based persons through the integration of artisanal excellence, sacrificial soul allocation, environmental failure analysis, and emotionally unsustainable succession planning.

2.3 Vision Statement

A world in which the earth learns what it can become, provided that at least one qualified individual remains willing to lose himself in increments.

