This recommendation is made despite the following:

* The maker will likely be reduced beyond recovery.
* The successor may reject the inherited purpose.
* The gods may claim success regardless of outcome.
* The work may not solve death, only distribute it more meaningfully.
* The distinction between sacrifice and exploitation remains procedurally unresolved.

These objections are serious and have therefore been entered into the record, where they can do the least harm.

