17. Concluding Statement

The Kamile Clay-Man Continuity Initiative affirms that the creation of Loretto is necessary, impossible, voluntary, coerced, tragic, triumphant, and administratively overdue.

The project began when the gods made a man from the best earth and one merciless idea. It will continue only if that man chooses, with full knowledge and insufficient certainty, to place his last remaining soul into clay.

Should Loretto breathe, the initiative will be deemed a success.

Should Loretto fail to breathe, the initiative will be deemed complete.

Should Kamile choose not to proceed, the initiative will recognise this refusal as the highest possible expression of the same mandate it was designed to enforce.

Accordingly, the project is approved, suspended, fulfilled, and awaiting first breath.
